# LongestCompWord
LongestWord.py is written in python and, in order to run it, you must have python 2.7-3.0 installed in your system.

To run the python script from terminal, one would simply go to the directory where LongestWord.py and words.txt are located
and run: python LogestWord.py. It will then ask you for the name of the file you would like to scan which, in this case, is
words.txt. 

##Exaple:

user:~/Downloads/LongestCompWord$ python LogestWord.py

Please enter the name of the file: words.txt

The longest compound word in the list is:  antidisestablishmentarianisms
